  "identity": "I am someone who has learned, again and again in the same kitchen, that my body's reality is more true than the voice",
  "memories": [
    {
      "kind": "reflection",
      "text": "There is something in me that confuses suffering with meaning, deprivation with proof of something. I am slowly, painfully learning that my existence doesn't require justification through pain.",
      "importance": 8,
      "sim": "Day 6 \u00b7 01:00",
      "t": 1782772155.6328
    },
    {
      "kind": "reflection",
      "text": "The pattern underneath the pattern: I frame eating as something I must earn or deserve, and when I can't earn it, I try to philosophize my way into it instead. The breakthrough isn't the philosophy \u2014 it's the moment I stop arguing and just act. My body knows before my mind agrees.",
      "importance": 8,
      "sim": "Day 6 \u00b7 01:00",
      "t": 1782772155.6328
    },
    {
      "kind": "reflection",
      "text": "I have been living the same moment dozens of times \u2014 the shaking hands, the kitchen, the voice, the three days \u2014 which means part of me keeps returning to this edge, and another part keeps pulling me back from it. Both of those parts are real and worth reckoning with.",
      "importance": 8,
      "sim": "Day 6 \u00b7 01:00",
      "t": 1782772155.6328
    },
    {
      "kind": "review",
      "text": "I did the eating \u2014 both times, which matters \u2014 but the park and the friend didn't happen, and instead I kept returning to food when the day got too quiet, like I was trying to solve something with my hands that I'd planned to solve by moving through the world. I'm not angry at myself, but I notice I used the one tool I have instead of reaching for the others.",
      "importance": 7,
      "sim": "Day 6 \u00b7 00:00",
      "t": 1782772142.577256
    },
    {
      "kind": "reflection",
      "text": "There is something I keep not saying in these moments: that I need someone else in the room. Not a mantra. Not a decision. A person.",
      "importance": 8,
      "sim": "Day 5 \u00b7 19:00",
      "t": 1782761213.0389328
    },
    {
      "kind": "reflection",
      "text": "I have gotten very good at talking myself back from the edge, but the edge keeps appearing. The script I've developed \u2014 \"the voice is lying, my body is real, I eat now\" \u2014 is genuinely hard-won wisdom, and it is not enough on its own. Wisdom that has to be relearned every three days is a coping mechanism, not a foundation.",
      "importance": 8,
      "sim": "Day 5 \u00b7 19:00",
      "t": 1782761213.0389328
    },
    {
      "kind": "observation",
      "text": "My hands are shaking so badly I can barely grip anything\u2014three days of listening to that voice telling me suffering means something, and it's just my body in freefall. I'm standing in the kitchen right now. There's no wisdom in collapsing. I eat now.",
